Date: Sun 22 Jan 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2017; 30(04) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=22476


Anthrax, Zambia
--------------------
Information received on [and dated] 22 Jan 2017 from Dr Yona Sinkala, Director, Department of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Fisheries and Livestock, Lusaka, Zambia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 12 Nov 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 28 Nov 2016
Report date: 22 Jan 2017
Date submitted to OIE: 22 Jan 2017
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 31 Mar 2016
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (5)
Outbreak 1: Sioma District, Kanja Vet Camp, Sioma, Western
Date of start of the outbreak: 12 Nov 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: other
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 6000 / 8 / 8 / 0 / 0
Affected population: cattle are under traditional management practicing free range grazing.

Outbreak 2: Limulunga District, Limulunga Vet Camp, Limulunga, Western
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Nov 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: other
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 12 000 / 4 / 4 / 0 / 0
Affected population: cattle are under traditional management practicing free range grazing.

Outbreak 3: Kalabo District, Nguma Vet Camp, Kalabo, Western
Date of start of the outbreak: 2 Dec 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: other
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 5500 / 5 / 5 / 0 / 0
Affected population: cattle are under traditional management practicing free range grazing.

Outbreak 4: Nalolo District, Kaunga Lueti Vet Camp, Nalolo, Western
Date of start of the outbreak: 04/12/2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: other
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 12 000 / 6 / 6 / 0 / 0
Affected population: cattle are under traditional management practicing free range grazing.

Outbreak 5: Shangombo District, Natukoma Vet Camp, Shangombo, Western
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Dec 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: other
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 11000 / 4 / 4 / 0 / 0
Affected population: cattle are under traditional management practicing free range grazing.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 5
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 46 500 / 27 / 27 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.06 / 0.06 / 100 / 0.06
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: anthrax is historically known to occur in Western Province. Vaccination has been carried out to contain the disease.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); disinfection/disinfestation; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Mongu Veterinary Laboratory (Local laboratory) / Cattle / microscopic examination / 28/11/2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

